1. What types of agentic systems are there?
  One differentiating feature of agentic systems is how they are “orchestrated” i.e. how do the agents carry out their tasks. Do they carry them out sequentially, in parallel, do they have autonomy to decide which tasks to runs or is it more prescribed?
  Some of the current patterns:
  1. Supervisor — where a central agent controls which of the sub-agents do what tasks etc.
  2. Sequential — where agents do their tasks linearally i.e. one after each other.
  3. Parallel — as you’d expect from the name, agents can run tasks at the same time.
  4. Swarm — a decentralised pattern, where agents work without a central command agent.
  5. Hierarchical — different layers of supervisor and sub-agents.
  6. Handoff — a pattern where an agent may decide to “handoff” the task to another agent (or human)
  These are actually just the tip of the iceberg. One of my favourite sayings has been for the last few months:
    “Nobody is an expert in GenAI or AgenticAI”
